30/06/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police used tear gas Tuesday (June 29th) against protestors in Athens who rallied as part of a strike against the government's austerity measures. 
The incident happened after about ten demonstrators started throwing stones, bottles, sticks and petrol bombs at police near the parliament building, where lawmakers began debating the planned austerity measures. 
(Reuters, AFP, Xinhua, BBC - 29/06/10)
